00:57.781 --> 01:01.281
== sync, corrected by <font color=#00ff00>elderman</font> ==

01:02.540 --> 01:05.876
Okay, okay,
okay, stop it!

01:05.910 --> 01:07.044
John's in there.

01:07.078 --> 01:08.679
And?

01:08.713 --> 01:13.684
And I have to
get home and change,

01:13.718 --> 01:17.287
and shower and, uh,
get him cleaned up

01:17.322 --> 01:18.488
and to the nursery and...

01:18.523 --> 01:19.656
Bye, bye, Mommy.

01:20.825 --> 01:22.025
Come, Mommy.

01:22.060 --> 01:23.861
Daddy will take you.

01:23.895 --> 01:25.596
Daddy will take you
to the nursery.

01:29.234 --> 01:30.934
I can't believe
we slept over here again.

01:30.969 --> 01:32.102
Why not?

01:32.136 --> 01:34.571
John likes sleeping over here.
And so do you.

01:34.606 --> 01:37.541
No, I love
sleeping over here.

01:37.575 --> 01:39.343
That's why I plan to
sleep over here all summer.

01:40.078 --> 01:43.180
But during the week, it makes
the mornings a little crazy.

01:43.214 --> 01:44.348
Or crazier.

01:44.382 --> 01:46.016
And it makes
the nights crazy too.

01:46.484 --> 01:47.651
Yeah.

01:47.685 --> 01:51.154
You know it would be easier
if you actually moved here.

01:51.189 --> 01:53.523
Brought the rest of your
things and John's things.

01:53.558 --> 01:54.992
You're practically
living here anyway.

01:55.026 --> 01:56.093
You're here all the time.

01:56.628 --> 01:58.462
I'm not here all the time.
Most of the time.

01:58.496 --> 02:00.530
For the past couple of months,
most of the time.

02:00.798 --> 02:04.234
Most of the time is not all of the time.
There's a big difference.

02:06.237 --> 02:08.372
I don't know.

02:08.406 --> 02:11.808
Ashley is taking off
with Toby today and...

02:11.843 --> 02:14.344
And you can't leave your dad
for the father of your son?

02:15.613 --> 02:18.515
Yeah, that doesn't
sound right, does it?

02:18.917 --> 02:20.817
No, it doesn't.

02:20.818 --> 02:23.086
And you can't let him tell you
that you have to stay there

02:23.121 --> 02:25.989
when he and your mom are letting
Ashley travel cross-country

02:26.024 --> 02:27.424
with her boyfriend
at 16.

02:27.458 --> 02:28.926
Yeah. She is.

02:29.727 --> 02:34.231
But, I mean, she graduated
from high school, technically.

02:34.265 --> 02:36.199
And she's too young
to go to college,

02:36.234 --> 02:37.367
even if she could get in.

02:38.236 --> 02:41.939
My mom thinks that it will teach
her the value of education,

02:41.973 --> 02:43.640
And that she'll learn
more about the United States

02:43.675 --> 02:44.775
seeing it than
reading about it.

02:45.276 --> 02:46.944
I can't believe
they're buying that.

02:46.978 --> 02:48.412
It's better for
two sixteen-year-olds

02:48.479 --> 02:50.213
to drive across the country
than go to school?

02:50.248 --> 02:52.950
Well, not all sixteen-year-olds,
just those two.

02:52.984 --> 02:55.218
I mean, maybe
it sounds little crazy,

02:55.253 --> 02:56.853
but, hey, so are we.

02:56.888 --> 02:58.455
I mean, I'm a junior
in high school

02:58.489 --> 03:01.959
and I'm actually thinking about
the three of us living together.

03:01.993 --> 03:04.361
Me and my baby
and the father of my baby.

03:04.395 --> 03:07.364
It's kind of surreal.

03:08.199 --> 03:09.466
I don't know.

03:09.500 --> 03:11.001
I feel as if
we're playing house

03:11.035 --> 03:14.972
more than I feel
that this is our house,

03:15.006 --> 03:16.340
and our family.

03:16.374 --> 03:18.608
I mean, if you want to make
it our house and our family.

03:18.643 --> 03:21.745
I do. I want you and
John to live here.

03:21.779 --> 03:23.647
The three of us together.

03:23.681 --> 03:25.682
It feels right.
It feels good even.

03:26.317 --> 03:29.987
We've been talking about this long enough.
Let's just do it. Move in.

03:30.021 --> 03:33.357
All right, what we've been talking
about is waiting until summer.

03:33.391 --> 03:35.625
Waiting until school is out
and then moving in together.

03:35.660 --> 03:37.794
I know, but it just hasn't
worked out that way.

03:37.829 --> 03:40.364
We're pretty much living together now.
The three of us.

03:42.133 --> 03:43.633
Okay.

03:43.668 --> 03:45.569
Now. Right now. Today.

03:46.104 --> 03:48.472
I said okay!

03:48.506 --> 03:50.974
As of today,
I live here.

03:51.009 --> 03:54.344
We live here.
John and me and you.

03:56.280 --> 03:58.615
Are you going to say anything
to your mom and dad?

03:58.649 --> 04:00.884
'Cause if you say
anything to either of them,

04:00.918 --> 04:02.552
you make a big
announcement or something,

04:02.587 --> 04:03.987
it's not going to happen.
You know that.

04:04.022 --> 04:06.456
You can't really expect them
to tell me that it's okay.

04:06.491 --> 04:08.759
Because it just wouldn't
be right for two parents

04:08.793 --> 04:10.994
to tell their teenage daughter that
she can live with her boyfriend.

04:11.029 --> 04:13.063
I think I'm a
little more than a boyfriend.

04:13.097 --> 04:14.831
Yeah, little more
than a boyfriend

04:14.866 --> 04:16.933
and a little less
than a husband.

04:16.968 --> 04:19.369
So, I don't think we're going
to get their approval.

04:20.171 --> 04:23.440
But we do have a son

04:24.208 --> 04:25.475
and I do love you.

04:27.145 --> 04:28.712
And like you said,

04:28.746 --> 04:31.615
we've been practically living here for
the past few months anyway. So...

04:31.649 --> 04:33.950
So, what's the
hesitation about?

04:33.985 --> 04:37.387
Just hope it doesn't seem
insensitive to other people.

04:37.422 --> 04:40.257
Insensitive, how?
To what other people?

04:40.291 --> 04:42.759
Adrian is going through
hell, and I'm not.

04:44.529 --> 04:45.796
I just feel
a little guilty

04:45.830 --> 04:47.564
that things worked out
so badly for them

04:47.598 --> 04:49.332
and not so badly for us.

04:49.367 --> 04:51.535
No, no, no.
You can't not move in with me

04:51.569 --> 04:54.704
because you feel guilty
about being happy, Amy.

04:54.739 --> 04:57.441
Whatever happens with
Ben and Adrian happens.

04:57.475 --> 04:59.743
Whatever that is,
it shouldn't affect us.

05:00.545 --> 05:04.014
I feel badly for both of
them, but I'm happy for us.

05:04.749 --> 05:07.284
The three of us,
we're a family.

05:07.952 --> 05:10.487
Yeah, we are a family,
aren't we?

05:10.521 --> 05:12.155
Yeah. We are, Amy.

05:12.190 --> 05:14.458
And I'm not going to
let anyone change that.

05:14.492 --> 05:16.693
And I'm not going to do anything
that would jeopardize that.

05:18.029 --> 05:19.229
Yeah, I know that.

05:22.733 --> 05:26.903
Well, I will see you tonight,
and I guess every night.

05:27.672 --> 05:28.939
Yeah, you will, Amy.

